About

Starting on ukulele at age 4 and exploring electric guitar at School of Rock, Aanya discovered a lasting voice in classical guitar. For the past decade, she has studied at the San Francisco Conservatory of Music Pre‑College, performing as soloist and in ensemble.

Her playing has earned international recognition, including selection as one of only five students worldwide for the 2024 Guitar Foundation of America Mentorship Program. She aspires to continue her musical education in college, focusing on performance and musical storytelling.

Highlights lyrical tremolo, rubato, and dynamic shaping across contrasting sections.
